# WHAT IT IS
#   HydraScript is "a TypeScript and Go inspired small
#   interpreted programming language written in C#".  Originally
#   started as a bachelor thesis "Extended JavaScript Subset",
#   it builds on the ECMA-262 standard with strong static
#   structural typing (no `class` / `interface` / `constructor`
#   keywords), forward references, compile-time runtime-error
#   detection, JavaScript-compatible lexical structure, and an
#   AOT-compiled native interpreter.  The reference
#   implementation includes a complete pipeline from Lexer →
#   Parser → CFG → SSA → DCE → AST-walking interpreter,
#   designed to be readable as a teaching tool for compiler
#   construction.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/HydraScript/
#                       ExecuteCommand.cs + Program.cs —
#                       System.CommandLine `RootCommand`)
#   hydrascript [OPTIONS] <PATH>
#
#   Positional:
#     <PATH>                         Path to input HydraScript
#                                    source file (`.js`)
#
#   Options:
#     -d, --dump, /d                 Show interpreter dump data
#                                    (token stream, parse tree,
#                                     CFG, SSA, etc.)
#                                    [default: false]
#
#   Standard System.CommandLine auto-flags:
#     -h, --help, /?                 Show help
#     --version                      Show version
#
# LANGUAGE-CORPUS POSITION
